cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.VIS, cs.SI, cs.DL

The paper discusses the design and use of glyphs for visualizing multivariate data, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), graphics (cs.GR), and visualization (cs.VIS). The paper also mentions applications in high energy physics and security, which could fall under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.DL) respectively.
